    "body": "For the following code, the implicit `drop(task)` emits vague `core::ptr::drop_in_place` while the instance name in backtrace is fully qualified as shown in https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/102\n\n```rust\n#[ostd::ktest::miri_main]\nfn kernel_main() {\n    println!(\"Hello world from guest kernel!\");\n    let task =\n        ostd::task::TaskOptions::new(|| ostd::miri_println!(\"A custom task from miri_main!\"))\n            .build()\n            .unwrap();\n}\n```\n\n<img width=\"3839\" height=\"2159\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9f47aefa-f388-4012-a39b-d187b5caf626\" />\n\n\n`after_grace_period` is called during task deallocation, but not listed:\n<img width=\"1116\" height=\"156\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c672487c-d350-4dc8-84e0-8c7e94111cb0\" />",
